This paper is about a toolkit for managing conversations between agents in multi-agent programming, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves software engineering (cs.SE) in terms of improving the reliability of agent communication. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of test subjects to evaluate the effectiveness of the toolkit, which suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect. Finally, the paper may also involve natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with managing conversations between agents.
